Document: Light2D
Path: godot/classes/class_light2d.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the Light2D node in Godot Engine.

Properties
* blend_mode (BlendMode): Controls how the light's color is blended with the existing colors on the screen. Default: 0.
* color (Color): The light's color. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
* editor_only (bool): If true, the light will only be visible in the editor. Default: false.
* enabled (bool): If true, the light is active. Default: true.
* energy (float): The strength of the light. Default: 1.0.
* range_item_cull_mask (int): Specifies which items this light should affect based on their cull mask. Default: 1.
* range_layer_max (int): The maximum layer index this light affects. Default: 0.
* range_layer_min (int): The minimum layer index this light affects. Default: 0.
* range_z_max (int): The maximum Z coordinate this light affects. Default: 1024.
* range_z_min (int): The minimum Z coordinate this light affects. Default: -1024.
* shadow_color (Color): The color of the light's shadow. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 0).
* shadow_enabled (bool): If true, shadows are cast by this light. Default: false.
* shadow_filter (ShadowFilter): The filter mode for the shadow. Default: 0.
* shadow_filter_smooth (float): The smoothness of the shadow filter. Default: 0.0.
* shadow_item_cull_mask (int): Specifies which items casting shadows this light should consider based on their cull mask. Default: 1.
---CHUNK---
Document: Light2D
Path: godot/classes/class_light2d.rst
Summary: This section details the methods and enumerations available for the Light2D class in Godot Engine.

Methods
Method: get_height() → float
Method: set_height(height: float)

Enumerations
enum ShadowFilter:
  SHADOW_FILTER_NONE = 0
    No filter applies to the shadow map. This provides hard shadow edges and is the fastest to render.
  SHADOW_FILTER_PCF5 = 1
    Percentage closer filtering (5 samples) applies to the shadow map. This is slower compared to hard shadow rendering.
  SHADOW_FILTER_PCF13 = 2
    Percentage closer filtering (13 samples) applies to the shadow map. This is the slowest shadow filtering mode, and should be used sparingly.

enum BlendMode:
  BLEND_MODE_ADD = 0
    Adds the value of pixels corresponding to the Light2D to the values of pixels under it. This is the common behavior of a light.
  BLEND_MODE_SUB = 1
    Subtracts the value of pixels corresponding to the Light2D to the values of pixels under it, resulting in inversed light effect.
  BLEND_MODE_MIX = 2
    Mix the value of pixels corresponding to the Light2D to the values of pixels under it by linear interpolation.
---CHUNK---
Document: Light2D
Path: godot/classes/class_light2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the Light2D node, controlling its appearance, behavior, and interaction with other nodes.

Inherits: CanvasItem

Properties:
- blend_mode (BlendMode): The Light2D's blend mode. Default: 0.
  - Setters: set_blend_mode(value: BlendMode)
  - Getters: get_blend_mode() -> BlendMode
- color (Color): The Light2D's color. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
  - Setters: set_color(value: Color)
  - Getters: get_color() -> Color
- editor_only (bool): If true, Light2D will only appear when editing the scene. Default: false.
  - Setters: set_editor_only(value: bool)
  - Getters: is_editor_only() -> bool
- enabled (bool): If true, Light2D will emit light. Default: true.
  - Setters: set_enabled(value: bool)
  - Getters: is_enabled() -> bool
- energy (float): The Light2D's energy value. The larger the value, the stronger the light. Default: 1.0.
  - Setters: set_energy(value: float)
  - Getters: get_energy() -> float
- range_item_cull_mask (int): The layer mask. Only objects with a matching CanvasItem.light_mask will be affected by the Light2D. See also shadow_item_cull_mask, which affects which objects can cast shadows. Default: 1.
  - Note: range_item_cull_mask is ignored by DirectionalLight2D, which will always light a 2D node regardless of the 2D node's CanvasItem.light_mask.
  - Setters: set_item_cull_mask(value: int)
  - Getters: get_item_cull_mask() -> int
- range_layer_max (int): Maximum layer value of objects that are affected by the Light2D. Default: 0.
  - Setters: set_layer_range_max(value: int)
  - Getters: get_layer_range_max() -> int
- range_layer_min (int): Minimum layer value of objects that are affected by the Light2D. Default: 0.
  - Setters: set_layer_range_min(value: int)
  - Getters: get_layer_range_min() -> int
- range_z_max (int): Maximum z value of objects that are affected by the Light2D. Default: 1024.
  - Setters: set_z_range_max(value: int)
  - Getters: get_z_range_max() -> int
- range_z_min (int): Minimum z value of objects that are affected by the Light2D. Default: -1024.
  - Setters: set_z_range_min(value: int)
  - Getters: get_z_range_min() -> int
- shadow_color (Color): Color of shadows cast by the Light2D. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 0).
  - Setters: set_shadow_color(value: Color)
  - Getters: get_shadow_color() -> Color
- shadow_enabled (bool): If true, the Light2D will cast shadows. Default: false.
  - Setters: set_shadow_enabled(value: bool)
  - Getters: is_shadow_enabled() -> bool
- shadow_filter (ShadowFilter): Shadow filter type. Default: 0.
  - Setters: set_shadow_filter(value: ShadowFilter)
  - Getters: get_shadow_filter() -> ShadowFilter
- shadow_filter_smooth (float): Smoothing value for shadows. Higher values will result in softer shadows, at the cost of visible streaks that can appear in shadow rendering. shadow_filter_smooth only has an effect if shadow_filter is SHADOW_FILTER_PCF5 or SHADOW_FILTER_PCF13. Default: 0.0.
  - Setters: set_shadow_smooth(value: float)
  - Getters: get_shadow_smooth() -> float
- shadow_item_cull_mask (int): The shadow mask. Used with LightOccluder2D to cast shadows. Only occluders with a matching CanvasItem.light_mask will cast shadows. See also range_item_cull_mask, which affects which objects can receive the light. Default: 1.
  - Setters: set_item_shadow_cull_mask(value: int)
  - Getters: get_item_shadow_cull_mask() -> int
